{
  "texts": [
    "This study explores the crucial role of international regulation in ensuring the safe and ethical use of Artificial Intelligence (AI), focusing specifically on the experience of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).",
    "As the importance of AI rapidly increases across various fields, such as healthcare, transportation, and energy, the need for comprehensive regulation becomes more apparent.",
    "This paper aims to investigate international responses to the development of AI technology and its societal and ethical impacts.",
    "Through the IAEA case study, it examines how international regulation can guarantee the safe use of AI and maximize the resulting societal benefits.",
    "The primary objective of this study is to analyze the regulatory framework of the IAEA as a model for AI governance."
  ]
}